Copyright is a bundle of rights that confers on its owners the rights to Reproduce the work,issue copies of the work to public, Communicate the work to public, Perform the work in public, Make any translation of the work, Make any adaptation of the work or Make cinematographic film or sound recording in respect of the work. Apart from the above, the following moral rights are also enjoyed by the author or copyright owner:
The right of publication: It is a right to decide whether or not to publish the work;
The right of paternity: It is a right to claim authorship for published or exhibited work;
The right of integrity: It is a right to prevent alteration and other actions that may damage the authors honor or reputation.

Statutory Fee (E-Filing) for Sound Recording: 2000(INR) per work;
Statutory Fee (E-Filing) for Literary Work and dramatic Work: 500(INR) per work;
Statutory Fee (E-Filing) for Cinematograph Film: 5000(INR) per work;
Statutory Fee (E-Filing) for artistic Film: 7000 (5000 for NOC and 2000 for filing application);
